==================================================
POST-MVP EXPANSION LAYER
EXECUTION ORCHESTRATION ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
The platform should evolve beyond:
- contract discovery
- qualification analysis
- proposal drafting

The platform should help users understand:
“How can this opportunity realistically be executed?”

==================================================
CORE PHILOSOPHY
==================================================

The platform should NOT:
- automatically execute contracts
- automatically hire vendors
- automatically sign agreements
- automatically submit proposals
- automatically commit pricing

The platform SHOULD:
- assist execution planning
- identify capability gaps
- identify subcontracting needs
- identify supplier needs
- identify staffing needs
- help users organize execution strategy

Human approval is ALWAYS required.

==================================================
CORE EXECUTION WORKFLOW
==================================================

1. Detect opportunity
2. Analyze opportunity
3. Determine opportunity category
4. Determine execution model
5. Compare against user capabilities
6. Detect missing capabilities
7. Search for subcontractors/vendors/suppliers
8. Generate execution recommendations
9. Generate outreach/contact lists
10. User performs follow-up
11. User gathers quotes/pricing
12. User finalizes proposal

==================================================
OPPORTUNITY CLASSIFICATION ENGINE
==================================================

The system should classify every contract opportunity into operational categories.

EXAMPLES:
- Technical Specialist
- Commodity Procurement
- Staffing
- Logistics
- Construction
- Research & Prototype
- Professional Services
- Manufacturing
- Training Systems
- IT Services
- Engineering Services
- AI/Automation
- Visualization/Simulation

==================================================
IMPORTANT SYSTEM RULE
==================================================

Each opportunity category should trigger DIFFERENT:
- qualification logic
- pricing logic
- execution analysis
- risk analysis
- supplier analysis
- subcontractor analysis
- proposal recommendations

The platform must NOT treat all opportunities the same.

==================================================
CAPABILITY GAP ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Determine what capabilities the user/company is missing in order to execute the opportunity.

WORKFLOW:
1. Parse contract requirements
2. Compare against user profile
3. Detect missing capabilities
4. Determine whether:
   - subcontractor required
   - supplier required
   - staffing required
   - teaming required

OUTPUT:
Capability Gap Report

==================================================
CAPABILITY GAP EXAMPLES
==================================================

EXAMPLES:
- Missing logistics capability
- Missing cloud infrastructure capability
- Missing cybersecurity certification
- Missing overseas support capability
- Missing tanker simulator experience
- Missing manufacturing capability

==================================================
SUBCONTRACTOR DISCOVERY ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Identify possible subcontractors that could help fulfill opportunity requirements.

EXAMPLES:
- XR specialists
- logistics providers
- cloud providers
- cybersecurity firms
- staffing companies
- manufacturing shops
- construction subcontractors

IMPORTANT:
The platform only recommends possible vendors/subcontractors.

The user is responsible for:
- outreach
- pricing negotiation
- legal agreements
- final selection

==================================================
SUPPLIER DISCOVERY ENGINE
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Help users identify suppliers required for commodity or procurement-based opportunities.

EXAMPLES:
- lumber suppliers
- hardware distributors
- commercial equipment vendors
- industrial suppliers
- material providers

WORKFLOW:
1. Analyze material requirements
2. Search regionally for suppliers
3. Rank supplier relevance
4. Generate supplier contact list

==================================================
STAFFING & TEAMING ANALYSIS
==================================================

PURPOSE:
Determine whether:
- staffing partnerships
- teaming arrangements
- operational partners

may be required.

EXAMPLES:
- overseas operational support
- large staffing requirements
- federal contract vehicle participation
- specialized certifications

==================================================
EXECUTION MODEL ENGINE
==================================================

The system should determine:
“How should this opportunity realistically be pursued?”

POSSIBLE OUTPUTS:
- Prime Contractor
